1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with binary codes and their rates, which is a topic closely related to information theory. 
2. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper involves the study of families of finite sets and their intersections, which is a topic in discrete mathematics. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The concept of cover-free codes has applications in cryptography and security, making this sub-category a likely fit. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper involves the study of codes and their properties, which can have implications for computational complexity. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The study of families of sets and their intersections can also be relevant to data structures and algorithms.
